src/lib/components/BaysanChart.react.js.description:
BaysanChart is an example of using Ant Design Charts component.
It takes a JSON data
to visualize.

id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

xField.description: The xField to use on the x-axis

yField.description: The yField to use on the y-axis

legendPosition.description: The legendPosition to set the position of the chart legend

src/lib/components/TextInput.react.js.description:
TextInput is an example component.
It takes a property, `label`, and
displays it.
It renders an input with the property `value`
which is editable by the user.

id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

label.description: The label used to show above of the input

value.description: The value used to set the default value for the input
